All four sitters and Aickman
were found dead.

515
00:55:40,876 --> 00:55:43,811
- Cause of death not clear.
- So Jonah killed them.

516
00:55:44,013 --> 00:55:45,640
Nobody knows. No sign of him.

517
00:55:45,848 --> 00:55:48,612
He was missing, vanished,
never seen again.

518
00:55:49,451 --> 00:55:50,418
Well, until now.

519
00:55:51,687 --> 00:55:54,656
Well, here's the weirdest part of all.
Okay, so 30 years later...

520
00:55:54,857 --> 00:55:56,688
... when they expanded the highway...

521
00:55:56,892 --> 00:55:58,450
... they did the detour through
the cemetery...

522
00:55:58,661 --> 00:56:00,720
Wait, we've been on that road
a million times.

523
00:56:00,929 --> 00:56:04,194
This is the thing: When they tried
to relocate some of the old plots...

524
00:56:04,400 --> 00:56:06,732
...they found something weird,
or didn't find.

525
00:56:06,935 --> 00:56:08,835
- What?
- Over a hundred bodies...

526
00:56:09,038 --> 00:56:11,871
...that were supposed to be there
weren't, just empty...

527
00:56:12,074 --> 00:56:13,507
...coffins filled with sandbags.

528
00:56:15,077 --> 00:56:16,704
Someone stole the bodies.

529
00:56:16,912 --> 00:56:18,846
Aickman.

530
00:56:19,048 --> 00:56:21,039
Or Jonah. Aickman or Jonah.

531
00:56:21,250 --> 00:56:22,979
Maybe, but why?

532
00:56:26,188 --> 00:56:31,125
I don't know,
but I might know somebody who does.

533
00:56:36,365 --> 00:56:38,799
- Remarkable.
- Do you think it's real?

534
00:56:39,268 --> 00:56:44,137
Well, I've seen plenty of fakes,
but I've seen the real thing once.

535
00:56:45,074 --> 00:56:46,803
Paris. It...

536
00:56:47,009 --> 00:56:51,844
It was the most horrible thing
I've ever seen, but not this.

537
00:56:52,047 --> 00:56:53,708
Must've been a very powerful medium.

538
00:57:31,987 --> 00:57:33,011
What are they?

539
00:57:33,222 --> 00:57:34,553
Eyelids.

540
00:57:35,924 --> 00:57:37,050
Human eyelids.

541
00:57:38,327 --> 00:57:39,419
Well, what are they for?

542
00:57:40,496 --> 00:57:42,521
Necromancy.

543
00:57:42,731 --> 00:57:44,255
Corpse-bothering.

544
00:57:45,701 --> 00:57:48,067
It's a loathsome form of magic.

545
00:57:48,270 --> 00:57:53,970
It's seeking power through control
of the dead via relics of their bodies.

546
00:57:54,176 --> 00:57:55,370
Well, why eyelids?

547
00:57:56,145 --> 00:57:57,942
That's a good question.

548
00:57:58,881 --> 00:58:01,975
I mean, traditionally we'd close the eyes
of the dead so they may...

549
00:58:02,184 --> 00:58:03,742
...rest in darkness.

550
00:58:03,952 --> 00:58:08,946
Now, removing their eyelids keeps
their eyes open, makes them see.

551
00:58:10,859 --> 00:58:13,692
Perhaps he intended them
to be watchmen...

552
00:58:14,630 --> 00:58:17,394
...or guardians of this house...

553
00:58:18,033 --> 00:58:19,398
...or of his secrets.

554
00:58:19,601 --> 00:58:22,035
By the way, I mean,
somewhere there are the bodies...

555
00:58:22,237 --> 00:58:26,105
...that belong to these people,
and he used them.

556
00:58:26,942 --> 00:58:30,844
I think ultimately, Aickman intended
to enhance Jonah's powers.

557
00:58:31,747 --> 00:58:33,942
Well, he amplified his seances.

558
00:58:34,149 --> 00:58:37,346
Somehow he bound the spirits of the
dead to their bodies, yes...

559
00:58:37,553 --> 00:58:41,683
...as an amplifier, probably through
some form of ritual or desecration.

560
00:58:43,492 --> 00:58:45,585
Perhaps buried outside the house?

561
00:58:50,465 --> 00:58:54,424
Perhaps it would help if we prayed
for all those poor souls that died here.

562
00:58:56,104 --> 00:58:57,867
For the boy too.

563
00:59:14,957 --> 00:59:16,049
Mommy?

564
00:59:16,258 --> 00:59:18,283
- Come back.
- Mommy?

565
00:59:19,628 --> 00:59:21,755
Please, please, help me.

566
00:59:29,771 --> 00:59:30,931
- Mommy.
- Help me.

567
00:59:33,275 --> 00:59:34,503
Matt.

568
01:00:08,210 --> 01:00:09,404
Matt.

569
01:00:38,407 --> 01:00:40,136
Matt. Who are you?

570
01:00:40,342 --> 01:00:41,775
What are you doing in my house?

571
01:00:41,977 --> 01:00:43,342
- Matt?
- I'm a reverend.

572
01:00:43,545 --> 01:00:45,103
It's okay. We asked him to come.

573
01:00:45,314 --> 01:00:46,781
- Asked him?
- We met at the...

574
01:00:46,982 --> 01:00:48,882
- Get out of my house.
- Get off. It's fine.

575
01:00:49,084 --> 01:00:51,245
We met at the hospital.
I receive treatment.

576
01:00:51,453 --> 01:00:53,614
- Get out.
- Well, he called me for advice.

577
01:00:53,822 --> 01:00:55,813
- It's a little hard to explain.
- Try.

578
01:00:56,024 --> 01:01:01,587
I believe that there is something evil
in this house...

579
01:01:01,797 --> 01:01:04,322
...something no longer living
and not yet passed over.

580
01:01:04,533 --> 01:01:05,898
And it wants your son.

581
01:01:06,101 --> 01:01:08,968
That's a dangerous situation
for someone who's close to death...

582
01:01:09,171 --> 01:01:10,399
He's not.

583
01:01:11,006 --> 01:01:16,467
And I'm as hopeful as you,
but tell me, have you not...

584
01:01:17,245 --> 01:01:19,679
...felt something strange here?

585
01:01:24,152 --> 01:01:26,086
I don't know what you're talking about.

586
01:01:26,288 --> 01:01:30,122
I appreciate the concern, but this is
not the type of help we need right now.

587
01:01:30,325 --> 01:01:32,259
I'd like you to leave.

588
01:01:32,761 --> 01:01:34,285
Of course.

589
01:01:41,436 --> 01:01:43,233
You're not alone.

590
01:03:43,892 --> 01:03:45,723
Peter?

591
01:03:54,903 --> 01:03:56,336
Matt?

592
01:04:34,876 --> 01:04:36,537
You're kidding.

593
01:04:38,046 --> 01:04:39,673
Hello!

594
01:04:39,881 --> 01:04:41,542
Anybody home?

595
01:04:41,750 --> 01:04:43,115
All the lights are on!

596
01:04:45,687 --> 01:04:47,712
Why are all the lights on?

597
01:04:49,558 --> 01:04:50,820
Ridiculous.

598
01:04:53,261 --> 01:04:54,819
Everybody in this house is sleeping...

599
01:04:55,063 --> 01:04:57,657
...with the lights on
and I wanna know why!

600
01:04:57,866 --> 01:04:59,891
He's been drinking.

601
01:05:01,736 --> 01:05:04,398
Why don't we just build a fire
and throw money into it?

602
01:05:05,106 --> 01:05:06,073
It's okay.

603
01:05:06,274 --> 01:05:08,902
I gotta pay a mortgage,
I'm now paying rent.

604
01:05:09,110 --> 01:05:10,839
Here's another one.

605
01:05:11,413 --> 01:05:13,142
God.

606
01:05:13,448 --> 01:05:17,544
Every single room has got a light on!

607
01:05:30,765 --> 01:05:33,063
Here. Here we go.

608
01:05:33,835 --> 01:05:35,666
Sleep in the dark.

609
01:05:47,415 --> 01:05:49,007
There we go.

610
01:05:49,217 --> 01:05:51,242
Lights out.

611
01:05:54,956 --> 01:05:56,787
There we go.

612
01:05:57,425 --> 01:05:59,052
Yeah.

613
01:06:03,765 --> 01:06:05,232
Peter...

614
01:06:06,234 --> 01:06:09,726
...that was a cruel
and childish thing to do.

615
01:06:10,705 --> 01:06:13,902
All you did was scare everybody
in this house.

616
01:06:16,011 --> 01:06:18,775
Don't. Don't. Don't.

617
01:06:22,550 --> 01:06:27,078
Your family needs your strength,
not your self-pity.

618
01:06:29,357 --> 01:06:33,657
You get drunk again, don't come home.

619
01:07:38,126 --> 01:07:39,593
Matt?

620
01:07:52,440 --> 01:07:53,407
Okay.

621
01:08:08,123 --> 01:08:10,353
I'm so sorry.
I just didn't know who else to call.

622
01:08:10,859 --> 01:08:11,985
It's all right.

623
01:08:12,193 --> 01:08:16,129
- Are you sure you're feeling up to this?
- Well, put it this way, I'm...

624
01:08:16,498 --> 01:08:19,592
I'm exactly the right state of being...

625
01:08:19,801 --> 01:08:21,359
...to traffic with ghosts.

626
01:08:26,908 --> 01:08:28,569
What is that?

627
01:08:29,210 --> 01:08:31,201
Magnets. Iron magnets.

628
01:08:31,413 --> 01:08:32,744
Iron defends from evil.

629
01:08:33,748 --> 01:08:37,616
So it's no accident
that prisons have iron bars...

630
01:08:37,819 --> 01:08:42,017
...to not merely contain the body,
but the evil that may lurk within it.

631
01:08:50,765 --> 01:08:53,029
- What are you looking for?
- Where he died.

632
01:08:54,903 --> 01:08:58,839
Sometimes when death is violent
or filled with anger...

633
01:08:59,040 --> 01:09:04,876
...or fear or any strong emotion...

634
01:09:06,314 --> 01:09:08,475
...it's as if the spirit doesn't pass on.

635
01:09:11,920 --> 01:09:16,721
That's why we cover mirrors,
light candles, open the shades...

636
01:09:16,925 --> 01:09:19,416
...so that they may find their way out.

637
01:09:19,761 --> 01:09:25,666
So a house with a trapped soul
is not so much haunted...

638
01:09:27,035 --> 01:09:29,595
...as it is possessed.

639
01:09:37,011 --> 01:09:39,309
What's down there?

640
01:09:40,348 --> 01:09:44,079
Matt's bedroom.
It's where they used to...

641
01:09:46,321 --> 01:09:48,551
Keep the children upstairs.

642
01:10:00,001 --> 01:10:01,127
Yeah.

643
01:10:01,336 --> 01:10:02,394
He's here.

644
01:10:02,604 --> 01:10:04,196
Do you see him, Matt?

645
01:10:06,574 --> 01:10:08,166
I don't see anything.

646
01:10:08,376 --> 01:10:11,971
That's because you're strong, you're
healthy. You shouldn't see anything.

647
01:10:44,212 --> 01:10:46,646
So this is where you're trapped.

648
01:10:49,083 --> 01:10:50,812
Don't worry.

649
01:10:51,686 --> 01:10:54,655
Whatever you may have done,
we're not here to punish you...

650
01:10:56,724 --> 01:10:59,090
...only to free you.

651
01:10:59,627 --> 01:11:01,527
Like a bird...

652
01:11:02,196 --> 01:11:04,460
...caught in a room.

653
01:11:17,679 --> 01:11:19,909
There must be another way.

654
01:11:20,148 --> 01:11:21,877
Perhaps the other side of that wall.

655
01:11:26,120 --> 01:11:30,079
I have to get his remains
out of the house.

656
01:11:49,677 --> 01:11:51,702
Stop it!

657
01:13:25,740 --> 01:13:26,968
It stopped.

658
01:13:45,693 --> 01:13:47,183
Will Matt be all right now?

659
01:13:47,395 --> 01:13:48,555
Yeah.

660
01:13:48,763 --> 01:13:50,526
The house is quiet and at peace.

661
01:13:51,165 --> 01:13:55,158
But I should warn you that sometimes
for a day or so after...

662
01:13:56,237 --> 01:14:01,140
...strange events, much like aftershocks
from an earthquake.

663
01:14:01,442 --> 01:14:04,138
But don't be alarmed...

664
01:14:04,612 --> 01:14:06,910
...it will pass,
within a day or two at the most.

665
01:14:17,892 --> 01:14:18,859
- Okay.
- All right.

666
01:14:21,329 --> 01:14:22,660
Thank you.

667
01:14:23,197 --> 01:14:24,926
It's okay.

668
01:14:27,235 --> 01:14:31,171
I wish I could say
it was my pleasure, but...

669
01:14:35,276 --> 01:14:36,607
You gonna be okay to drive?

670
01:14:36,811 --> 01:14:39,245
We're all in God's hands.

671
01:15:10,578 --> 01:15:13,046
It's only five more sleeps
till parents' day.

672
01:15:13,247 --> 01:15:15,215
I can't wait.
I got a lot to show you, Dad.

673
01:15:15,416 --> 01:15:17,441
You'll see
how I shoot the bow and arrow...

674
01:15:17,652 --> 01:15:21,884
... and how far I can swim
and they're having a father-son race.

675
01:15:22,089 --> 01:15:23,113
It's gonna be great.

676
01:15:23,324 --> 01:15:26,418
I bet you and me,
we beat all the others...

677
01:15:26,627 --> 01:15:29,892
... unless you're too old
and broke down.

678
01:15:30,097 --> 01:15:33,692
Okay, well, I better go. Bye, Dad.

679
01:15:36,704 --> 01:15:39,867
All right,
whatever was here is gone now.

680
01:15:40,074 --> 01:15:42,372
Now, we've all had
some really bad nights.

681
01:15:58,793 --> 01:16:00,055
Stay here.

682
01:16:03,731 --> 01:16:05,028
Oh, my God.

683
01:16:05,233 --> 01:16:07,394
Oh, my... Oh, my...

684
01:16:08,603 --> 01:16:11,197
Oh, my God.
What have you done to yourself?

685
01:16:15,943 --> 01:16:19,470
All right, I'm gonna follow them. When
I get back, we're getting out of here.

686
01:18:14,929 --> 01:18:16,760
Sir?

687
01:18:17,798 --> 01:18:20,631
They'll be after you now.

688
01:18:20,835 --> 01:18:22,268
Get out.

689
01:19:00,474 --> 01:19:01,634
Somebody help me!

690
01:19:11,552 --> 01:19:15,818
Please! Somebody help me!

691
01:20:13,080 --> 01:20:14,377
Where's Matt?

692
01:20:14,582 --> 01:20:16,072
He's at the hospital.

693
01:20:16,283 --> 01:20:19,480
The doctors are gonna
take care of him, okay?

694
01:21:08,836 --> 01:21:11,396
Hi. We're not home right now,
so please leave a message.

695
01:21:11,605 --> 01:21:12,833
Thanks.

696
01:21:14,542 --> 01:21:17,010
I made a terrible mistake.

697
01:21:17,211 --> 01:21:20,544
Aickman didn't remove their eyelids
to make the dead see...

698
01:21:20,748 --> 01:21:22,682
...but to make them unseen.

699
01:21:22,883 --> 01:21:25,215
So all those missing bodies...

700
01:21:25,786 --> 01:21:29,347
...all those poor souls in torment,
they're still there. They're in the house.

701
01:21:29,890 --> 01:21:33,451
But the boy wasn't evil.

702
01:21:33,694 --> 01:21:35,457
He was trying to free them.

703
01:21:35,663 --> 01:21:36,960
And I removed him.

704
01:21:39,533 --> 01:21:41,694
Now all that's left is their rage.

705
01:21:42,236 --> 01:21:43,635
You must get out now.

706
01:21:45,673 --> 01:21:47,231
Get out now.

707
01:22:27,615 --> 01:22:29,173
I'm sorry.

708
01:22:30,884 --> 01:22:33,853
It's okay. You're here now.
That's all that matters.

709
01:22:37,858 --> 01:22:40,725
He's sedated and comfortable.

710
01:22:41,328 --> 01:22:42,727
We ran his panels.

711
01:22:43,764 --> 01:22:45,698
I'm afraid it's not good news.

712
01:22:45,899 --> 01:22:47,594
His cell count is worse than before.

713
01:22:48,002 --> 01:22:51,267
The treatment has, frankly,
had no effect.

714
01:22:54,241 --> 01:22:55,970
How long do you think he has?

715
01:22:56,176 --> 01:22:59,077
With these numbers,
I don't know what's keeping him alive.

716
01:22:59,280 --> 01:23:01,180
He could go tonight.

717
01:23:01,382 --> 01:23:04,078
There's really no way of saying for sure.

718
01:23:06,320 --> 01:23:07,912
Then can we see him?

719
01:23:08,756 --> 01:23:10,587
Of course.

720
01:23:12,359 --> 01:23:13,519
To fight.

721
01:23:13,727 --> 01:23:15,558
One bright day
In the middle of the night

722
01:23:15,763 --> 01:23:17,788
Two dead boys got up to fight

723
01:23:17,998 --> 01:23:19,260
He couldn't have gotten far.

724
01:23:19,466 --> 01:23:21,991
- One bright day in the middle...
- Hi, this is Dr. Brooks.

725
01:23:22,202 --> 01:23:23,965
Get me security right away, please.

726
01:23:24,171 --> 01:23:25,798
Two dead boys got up to fight

